data.text:
[Verse 1]
The pavement hums a quiet tune tonight
Streetlights glow like fireflies in their flight
The city's pulse beats soft under the dark
A symphony of lives
A fleeting spark

[Verse 2]
The windows flicker dreams behind the glass
Whispers blend with footsteps as they pass
The world slows down
It sheds its heavy coat
Underneath the moon
We gently float

[Chorus]
Peaceful nights under city skies
Stars wink down
Watching life arise
Breath of calm in a dance of light
Oh
City dreams in the quiet night

[Verse 3]
The skyline hums
A sleeping lullaby
Soft winds carry stories whispered by
Neon signs reflecting on the stream
Life is breathing softly in this dream

[Bridge]
The chaos melts in shadows
Fades away
Night's embrace singing songs of yesterday
The world finds peace beneath its sprawling wings
In the city's stillness
The soul softly sings

[Chorus]
Peaceful nights under city skies
Stars wink down
Watching life arise
Breath of calm in a dance of light
Oh
City dreams in the quiet night
data.title: City Lights Serenade

data.text:

Their whispers brush the midnight's brim
Footsteps fade like echoes sigh
Underneath the velvet sky

[Chorus]
The city's heart beats low and slow
A secret rhythm only night can show
Neon dreams in shadows play
Guiding stars in lost café

[Verse 2]
Window panes hold stories close
Tangled tales the moonlight knows
Silent cars hum distant tunes
Guarded by the watching moon

[Bridge]
Concrete jungle learns to rest
Its weary soul now feels its best
A peace so rare it fills the air
Soft sighs of calm are everywhere

[Chorus]
The city's heart beats low and slow
A secret rhythm only night can show
Neon dreams in shadows play
Guiding stars in lost café

[Outro]
At quiet's peak the dawn will call
But for now the city's walls hold all
A soothing hymn no one can fight
This perfect still this peaceful night
